MAILS.subject: Trump Won’t Certify Nuclear Deal, but Won’t Unravel It
MAILS.content: President Trump’s decision not to certify that Iran was complying with all terms of the 2015 agreement reached by President Barack Obama came after a fierce debate inside the administration.

MAILS.subject: Wolf Puppies Are Adorable. Then Comes the Call of the Wild.
MAILS.content: When they are full-grown at around 100 pounds, their jaws will be strong enough to crack moose bones. But because these wolves have been around humans since they were blind, deaf and unable to stand, they will still allow people to be near them, to do veterinary exams, to scratch them behind the ears — if all goes well.

MAILS.subject: In California, Fires So Fast Hesitation Proved Lethal
MAILS.content: By THOMAS FULLER and RICHARD PÉREZ-PEÑA 12:00 AM ET. As stories emerged of how people died in the wind-driven fires that have ravaged Northern California, the element common to each tragedy was how quickly it happened.

MAILS.subject: At This Brooklyn Bar, It’s Just You, Your Date and the Barman
MAILS.content: Public drinking in New York can be a chore. Many of the city’s bars are about as intimate as a rush-hour subway. Others serve as the stalking grounds for happy-hour predators. When the suits and ties arrive, it can be hard to find a stool or to get your glass refilled.
